The paper focuses on collision checking and motion planning for robots, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of a neural network for collision checking suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of parallel computing and adaptive thresholding, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), respectively. Finally, the experiments on a physical robot suggest the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category as a possibility.
